HEADWORD: icehouse
<hw>ice"house`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a building used for storing ice,
especially one built partly below ground and insulated so as to preserve
ice obtained during the winter from frozen lakes or rivers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

